From Gordon Banks Subject Re amitriptyline In article M Eric Roberts writes Could someone please tell me, what effect an overdose mg of amitriptyline would have Probably would not be fatal in an adult at that dose, but could kill a child Patient would be very somnolent, with dilated pupils, low blood pressure Possibly cardiac arrhythmias Gordon Banks N JXP Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect, and it is shameful to surrender it too soon